# 68k Assembly Guide

## Intent
Provide the conventions for writing readable Motorola 68000 assembly that feeds into the Amiga/Genesis subtrees (`games/m68k/` and `games/genesis/`). Keep directives grouped, macros brief, and maintain consistent indentation.

## Key Tips
- Use `org`, `section`, and `align` directives to pin data to the correct banks (Chip RAM vs. Fast RAM). Mention the intended memory region in comments.
- Prefer long labels (`main_loop`, `vblank_wait`) and group register saves/restores near the joystick/palette handling logic.
- Document calling conventions at the top of each file: which registers you preserve (`d0-d2`, `a0-a3`), where stack frames live, and how parameters arrive.

## Toolchain Sample
```sh
nasm -f aout -o build/init.o src/m68k/init.s
gcc build/main.o build/init.o -o bin/game -m68000
```

## Reuse & Replication
- Store reusable copper lists, blitter command blocks, and interrupt vectors inside `data/` and reference them via `.inc` files documented here.
- Note any platform-specific assembler macros in a `macros/` subdir so the tour can reference them from `.documentation/68k/index.mdc`.
